14/08/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- The Turkish Security Directorate's intelligence and anti-terrorism departments issued a warning Wednesday (13 August), urging Ankara police to be on alert for terrorist attacks. The letter warns of a possible escalation in terrorist activity following implementation of the new amnesty law for suspected members of the KADEK group, formerly known as the PKK, as well as political prisoners. The alert noted that terrorist organisations plan to continue attacks on state institutions, particularly police centres. (Anadolu Agency - 13/08/03)
